        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Logarithm is a multivalued function: for each "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "x"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " there is an infinite\nnumber of "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "z"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " such that "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "2**z = x"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ". The convention is to return the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "z"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nwhose imaginary part lies in "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "(-pi, pi]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "For real-valued input data types, "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/log2",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "log2",
                "text": "log2"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " always returns real output.\nFor each value that cannot be expressed as a real number or infinity,\nit yields "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "nan"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and sets the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "invalid"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " floating point error flag."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "For complex-valued input, "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/log2",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "log2",
                "text": "log2"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is a complex analytical function that\nhas a branch cut "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "[-inf, 0]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and is continuous from above on it. "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/log2",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "log2",
                "text": "log2"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nhandles the floating-point negative zero as an infinitesimal negative\nnumber, conforming to the C99 standard."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "In the cases where the input has a negative real part and a very small\nnegative complex part (approaching 0), the result is so close to "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "-pi"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nthat it evaluates to exactly "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "-pi"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import whest as we"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x = we.array([0, 1, 2, 2**4])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.log2(x)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([-inf,   0.,   1.,   4.])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "xi = we.array([0+1.j, 1, 2+0.j, 4.j])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.log2(xi)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([ 0.+2.26618007j,  0.+0.j        ,  1.+0.j        ,  2.+2.26618007j])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
